              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9653496-hanne?shelf=abandoned">abandoned</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer396324087" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6604464645082448996">Ooooo Mr Eco, always trying to be smart and complex; always showing off your encyclopedian knowledge of history and philisophy. I liked you well enough in &apos;The Name of the Rose&apos;, but I couldn&apos;t stand you in &apos;Baudolino&apos;.<br/><br/>Never has an author made me feel so stupid, unknowledgeable and insignificant. As if someone who doesn&apos;t know everything you know, isn&apos;t worthy of walking the planet and reading your books. As if you know everything you wrote about by heart! You probably had to look it up too, so </span>
  <span id="freeText6604464645082448996" style="display:none">Ooooo Mr Eco, always trying to be smart and complex; always showing off your encyclopedian knowledge of history and philisophy. I liked you well enough in 'The Name of the Rose', but I couldn't stand you in 'Baudolino'.<br /><br />Never has an author made me feel so stupid, unknowledgeable and insignificant. As if someone who doesn't know everything you know, isn't worthy of walking the planet and reading your books. As if you know everything you wrote about by heart! You probably had to look it up too, so please give your reader some help.<br /><br />Trying to get through the first 100 pages was like the most complex history exam I ever had.<br /><br />And I did not enjoy it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6604464645082448996" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
