<span id="freeTextContainer4452501224309913848">Baudolino is a liar. His life is a picaresque and often amusing novel where History mixes with history. What&apos;s more funny for me, it is the relics traffic. At the middle-âge, it was a very profitable buisness. There is a joke : it was said that, with all authentics pieces of the Jesus&apos;s cross carefully collected in the churches, we could build an arch for Noé. <br/>Style is beautiful, it is magnificiently written. It is felt that Eco take pleasure to write it, Eco let him go. Then, truth or lie? No i</span>
  <span id="freeText4452501224309913848" style="display:none">Baudolino is a liar. His life is a picaresque and often amusing novel where History mixes with history. What's more funny for me, it is the relics traffic. At the middle-âge, it was a very profitable buisness. There is a joke : it was said that, with all authentics pieces of the Jesus's cross carefully collected in the churches, we could build an arch for Noé. <br />Style is beautiful, it is magnificiently written. It is felt that Eco take pleasure to write it, Eco let him go. Then, truth or lie? No importance. Alexandre Dumas said "We can cheat on the History on condition that it's to make her beautiful children." This one is splendid.</span>
